claim.claim-text:
1. A light emitting device comprising:
a substrate;
a first insulating layer over the substrate;
a semiconductor layer including a channel region over the first insulating layer;
a gate insulating film over the semiconductor layer;
a gate electrode over the gate insulating film;
a second insulating layer covering the gate electrode;
a first opening in the second insulating layer;
a first electrode in the first opening and over the second insulating layer so as to be in contact with the first insulating layer;
a bank layer covering the second insulating layer and the first electrode, wherein the bank layer has a second opening so as to expose the first electrode, and wherein the second opening overlaps with the first opening;
a light emitting layer over the first electrode which is exposed in the second opening; and
a second electrode over the light emitting layer,
wherein the first electrode includes a conductive substance having light transmitting properties.

4. A light emitting device comprising:
a substrate;
a first insulating layer over the substrate;
a semiconductor layer including a channel region over the first insulating layer;
a gate insulating film over the semiconductor layer;
a gate electrode over the gate insulating film;
a second insulating layer covering the gate electrode;
a first opening and a second opening in the second insulating layer;
a wiring connected to the semiconductor layer through the first opening;
a first electrode connected to the wiring, wherein the first electrode is in contact with the first insulating layer in the second opening;
a bank layer covering the second insulating layer and the first electrode, wherein the bank layer has a third opening so as to expose the first electrode, and wherein the third opening overlaps with the second opening;
a light emitting layer over the first electrode which is exposed in the third opening; and
a second electrode over the light emitting layer.

8. A light emitting device comprising:
a substrate;
a first insulating layer on the substrate;
a second insulating layer on the first insulating layer;
a semiconductor layer including a channel region over the second insulating layer;
a gate insulating film over the semiconductor layer;
a gate electrode over the gate insulating film;
a third insulating layer covering the gate electrode;
a first opening in the third insulating layer;
a first electrode in the first opening so as to be in contact with the first insulating layer;
a bank layer covering the second insulating layer;
a second opening in the bank layer, wherein the second opening overlaps with the first opening;
a light emitting layer being in contact with the first electrode exposed in the second opening; and
a second electrode over the light emitting layer.
